<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 4:04PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT
NORTHWESTERN ROANOKE...SOUTHEASTERN CRAIG AND NORTHEASTERN MONTGOMERY
COUNTIES THROUGH 430 PM EDT...
At 404 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bradshaw, or near Catawba, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Catawba...
Abbott...
Mc Donalds Mill...
and Bradshaw.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
